assignment of a dedicated member of the care team or case manager; proactive 
dissemination of information, education and psychosocial support; access to 
objective assessment of neuropsychological functioning; facilitating easier 
access to welfare payments; and services facilitating communication about 
difficult illness-related topics. Provision of services along these 
recommendations could improve supportive care of brain tumour patients and their 
carers.

