Slipping through the cracks. Dental care for older persons with intellectual 
disabilities.

Waldman HB(1), Truhlar MR, Perlman SR.

Author information:
(1)Department of General Dentistry, State University at Stony Brook School of 
Dental Medicine, USA.

An increasing population of men and women with intellectual disabilities and 
other developmental disabilities is reaching older ages. As our country 
continues the process of deinstitutionalization, these individuals will require 
treatment in communities. Dental practitioners increasingly will be involved in 
the needs of this population, many of whom are members of families being treated 
in private dental practices. A review of these developments and the particular 
dental needs of these patients is considered.

